Consider the problem of defining the `mem_support_selectElem` field for the `SampleableType (Vector α n)` instance. The support of the `selectElem` computation for `n + 1` (the `succ` case) is the set of vectors formed by pushing an element from the support of `$ᵗ α` onto a vector from the support of the recursive call. Since both supports are universal, any vector `x : Vector α (n + 1)` is in the support if it can be decomposed into a prefix `x.pop` and a last element `x.back`, such that pushing `x.back` onto `x.pop` yields `x`. This identity is given by `Vector.push_pop_back x`.

